its an uphill battle for lupe valdez, the democratic gubernatorial candidate in texas, a state that hasnt elected a democrat to statewide office in nearly half a century.but valdez is used to uphill battles  shes the states first openly gay and first latina sheriff. valdez joined nbc news think, nbc out and nbc latino to talk about a range of issues including healthcare, the importance of fostering trust between members of law enforcement and the community and the challenges of running as a democrat in a conservative state like texas.watch the full interview with valdez above.